        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add `agents.defaults.imageQuality` with `auto`, `efficient`, `balanced`, and `high` modes\n- make image-tool media loading choose an adaptive compression grid from the selected image model, image count, and fallback candidates\n- document the new setting and cover provider/model-aware grids, model overrides, and fallback-safe caps\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/media/web-media.test.ts src/agents/tools/image-tool.test.ts src/config/schema.help.quality.test.ts` (4 files, 205 passed)\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` (clean: no accepted/actionable findings)\n- `pnpm check:changed` on Blacksmith Testbox `tbx_01ksamgparkanfys6v84179zt8`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Image-tool compression now adapts to the configured image quality preference and selected vision model while capping to the safest candidate when model fallbacks are possible.\nReal environment tested: Local focused Vitest plus Blacksmith Testbox changed gate.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/media/web-media.test.ts src/agents/tools/image-tool.test.ts src/config/schema.help.quality.test.ts`; `pnpm check:changed`.\nEvidence after fix: Focused tests passed 205 tests; Blacksmith Testbox `tbx_01ksamgparkanfys6v84179zt8` exited 0.\nObserved result after fix: Model-aware grids select larger caps for documented high-capability models, many-image auto mode switches efficient, and fallbacks/overrides cap compression to the smaller candidate before image loading.\nWhat was not tested: Live provider calls with real image uploads were not run; this patch validates local compression policy and the affected type/lint/test lanes.\n",
